ich die ‚Mietkasernenstadt‘ und das Verschwinden ‚Alt-Berlins‘ darstellten, bilden die dritte Perspektive. Und wie blickte das späte 19. Jahrhundert durch die Literatur auf Zeiten zurück, in denen Perspektiven Deutschlands sich eng mit denen der Stadt verbanden?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aBaillot, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerbig, Roland, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerbig, Roland, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBlänkner, Reinhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBodenschatz, Harald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBriese, Olaf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBusch, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBöhm, Manuela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarr, Gilbert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aD\x27Aprile, Iwan-Michelangelo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aD´Aprile, Iwan-M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFischer, Hubertus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFähnders, Walter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGörner, Rüdiger, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHermand, Jost, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKöhler, Astrid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKöstler, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLehnert, Gertrud, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/re